obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE BOMABY RENT - FREE ESTATES ACT, 185 2`
  line `A CT N O. XI OF 18 5 2`
  line `[ Passed on the 1 3 t h February, 185 2.]`
  line `Recites expediency of providing means of settling claims against Government in certain districts: and`
  line `that rules of Bombay R. 17, 1827, Chap. 9, 10, and R. 6, 1833, Cl. 1. Do not apply to districts not under`
  line `Government Regulations: enacts.`
  line `1. No order of Government regarding title to lands in any of the non - regulation dist r icts shall be`
  line `questioned in any Court of law on ground of inconsistency with this Act.`
  line `2, 3. Governor of Bombay may appoint in recited districts an Inam Commissioner with assistants:`
  line `who ( 3 ) shall discharge their duties according to rules in Schedule to this Act.`
  line `4. Claims to exemption shall be determined according to Rules in Schedule B.`
  line `5. Each Inam Commissioner to have same authority for examination of witnesses and taking evidence`
  line `and inflicting penalties as the Civil Courts.`
  line `6. Bribery, extortion and generally all act of abuse under the Commission shall be punishable as`
  line `cri minal offences without prejudice to civil remedy.`
  line `7. No decision of Inam Commissioner, & c. shall be questioned in Court of law.`
  line assistants.
  line `Rule 1. Defines the functions of the Inam Commissioner and his assistants.`
  line `Rule 2. Gives appeal against orders of Assistant Commissioner.`
  line `Rule 3. And subsequent rules prescribe the mode of proceeding to es tablish claims.`
  line `Schedule B. Rules for adjudication of title to estates claimed as Inam.`
  line `Rule 1. Confines all Inams already declared permanent by competent authority competency of officer`
  line `shall be decided if questioned.`
  line `Rule 2. Land to be hereditary if expressly made so by Sunnud, provided, (1) that Sunnud was made by`
  line `competent authority; (2) that no illegal conditions are attached to the tenure; and (3) that is was not reoked,`
  line `& c.`
  line `Rule 3. An uninterrupted holdi ng for 60 years before the introduction of heir in possession all the time.`
  line `Th e right not to descend on heirs y adoption, not on femal e heirs.`
  line `Rule 4. Lands held for 40 years in the male line to continue to be held for one more generation; but not`
  line `by an adopted heir; (1) what shall be sufficient proof of authorized possession; (2)claim to be allowed`
  line `unless to grounds of it be disproved; and (3) what shall be deemed the time of the introduction of British`
  line Government.
  line `Rule 5. None so numbered.`
  line `Rule 6. Exemptions not protected by above rules to be abolished on demise of incumbent: and ( 1 ) bond`
  line `fide holder to be deemed incumbent; ( 2 ) this privilege not to ext end to persons holding by fraud.`
  line `Rule 7. Lands h e ld for support of Mosques, & c. not to be resumed. (4) if they have been enjoyed for`
  line `40 years; (5) What shall be deemed sufficient proof of enjoyment; (6) but this rule not to apply in f avor of`
  line `private holdings (7) see the provision.`
  line `Rule 8. Lands held under on official tenure intended to be permanent not to be resumed; but this rule`
  line `is subject to several complicated provisions, not capable of abridgment.`
  line `Rule 9. On resumption of lands a moiety may be continued to widows of last incumbent, &c. in case of`
  line destitution.
  line `Rule 10. Makes discretionary with Government to apply these rules to certain specified kinds of lands.`
  line `Rule 11. Empowers the G. in C. to relax the rules; who also shall inter pret them.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
