obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `An Act for the Adjudication of Titles to certain Estates claimed to be wholly or partially Rent - free in`
  line `the Presidency of Bombay.`
  line `W HEREAS in the Territories of the Deccan Kandeish, and Southern Mahratta Country, and in other`
  line `Districts more rec ently annexed to the Bombay Presidency, claims against Government on account of Inams`
  line `and other Estates wholly or partially exempt from payment of Land Revenue are excepted from the`
  line `cognizance of the ordinary Civil Courts, and incapable of being justly dis posed of under the Rules for the`
  line `determination of Titles, and the Rules of Procedure contained in Chapters IX. and X. of Regulation X V II.`
  line `of 1827 of the Bombay Code and their Supplements; and whereas it is desirable that the said claims should`
  line `be tried and determined without further delay. It is declared and enacted as follows:`
  line `I. The Rules in Chapters IX. and X. of Regulation X V II. of 1827, and in Clause 1 of Regulation`
  line `VI. of 1833 of the Bombay Code, do not apply to any of the Districts of the Bombay Presidency which`
  line `were not brought under the General Regulations of Government by Regulation XX V III. of 1827 of the`
  line `Bombay Code; and no order hitherto passed regarding the continuance or resumption of lands in any of the`
  line `said Districts held or claim ed from Government as wholly or partially free of assessment, shall be liable to`
  line `be questioned in any Court of Law, on the grounds of any interpretation nr construction of the Law, which`
  line `may be inconsistent with the declarations made and the rules prescrib ed by this enactment.`
  line `II. The Governor of Bombay in Council may appoint in any Zillah or other division of the Territories`
  line `subject to the Presidency of Bombay, which were not brought under the General Regulations of`
  line `Government by the said Regulation XXVIII. of 1827, an Inam Commissioner with so many Assistants, and`
  line `such subordinate Establishment, as may be necessary for the purposes hereinafter mentioned.`
  line `III. The duties of each Inam Commissioner and his Assistants shah be discharged according to the`
  line `Rules in Schedule A. annexed to this Act.`
  line `IV. In the adjudication of claims to exempt lands or interests therein, the titles of claimants shall he`
  line `determined by the Rules in Schedule B. annexed to this Act.`
  line `V. Each Inam Commissioner sand his Assistants shall hav e the same authority to procure the attendance`
  line `of witnesses, and to take evidence, as now is, or from time to time may be, by Law vested in the ordinary`
  line `Civil Courts; and so far as concerns the penalties for not giving evidence, for false testimony, for re sistance`
  line `of process, contempts, and other like matters, connected with cases under cognizance by any one of the said`
  line `Officers, his Office shall be held to be a Court of Civil Jurisdiction of the same authority as the superior`
  line `Civil Court of the Zillah or D istrict in which his Office from time to time shall be established. Provided`
  line `that all complaints against, or appeals from the proceedings of the Inam Commissioner or any of his`
  line `Assistants, in exercise of the authority conferred on them respectively by this Section, shall be made under`
  line `the second Rule of Schedule A. annexed to this Act, and shall not be cognizable by any other authority or`
  line `in any other manner than as therein specified.`
  line `VI. Bribery, extortion, and generally all acts of abuse, or misapplicatio n of authority, or other`
  line `misconduct, committed by any Officer belonging to the Establishment of the Inam Commission, or`
  line `temporarily employed therein under the provisions of this enactment, shall be punishable as criminal`
  line `offences with fine and ordinary imp risonment without labour for a period not exceeding five years, and the`
  line `receipt of a present, directly or indirectly, by any such Officer from any person against whom or in whose`
  line `behalf he may be officially employed, shall be considered extortion. And no p enalty or punishment`
  line `adjudicated under this Clause shall preclude any other Civil prosecution to which the offender may be`
  line liable.
  line `VII. No decision or order of the Inam Commissioner, or of any of his Assistants, or of the Governor in`
  line `Council, under the pro visions of this enactment, so long as the same shall be in force under such provisions,`
  line `shall be questioned or avoided in any Court of Law; and no Commissioner or Assistant Commissioner, or`
