  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `SCHEDULE A`
  line `Rules for defining the duties of each I nam commissioner and his assistants`
  line `1. The duty of the Inam Commissioner and his Assistants shall be to investigate, in the manner`
  line `prescribe d by this enactment, the titles of persons holding or claiming against Government the possession`
  line `or enjoyment of Inams or Jagheers, or any interest therein, or claiming exemption from the payment of`
  line `Land Revenue, and generally to act according to the instr uctions of Government in all matters not`
  line `specifically provided for in this enactment.`
  line `2. All orders of the Assistant Commissioners shall be appealable to the Inam Commissioner, who shall`
  line `also have the authority of revising and of modifying, reversing or an nulling, if necessary, their orders and`
  line `proceedings, and the orders and proceedings of the Inam Commissioner shall be in like manner appealable`
  line `to, and subject to modification, reversal, or annulment by the Governor of Bombay in Council, whose orders`
  line `shall in every case be final.`
  line `3. The Inam Commissioner or his Assistants shall receive from the persons holding or claiming to hold`
  line `lands or any interest therein exempt from the payment of Revenue, statements explaining the nature of the`
  line `title by which the land s or interests are so held, and shall take and record the evidence offered in support of`
  line `such statements.`
  line `4. These statements may be received, either directly by the Officers of the Inam Commission, or through`
  line `the medium of the Revenue Authority of the Tal ooka in which the land or interest so held or claimed as`
  line `exempt is situated; or in which the alleged proprietor resides, without any previous procedure, except a`
  line `general invitation to such landholders of a District who shall hold or claim to hold lands exe mpt as aforesaid`
  line `to state the nature of their titles.`
  line `5. But when such general invitation is not sufficiently attended to, a notice may be issued to any party`
  line `holding or claiming to hold any lands or any interest therein wholly or partially exempt as afore said,`
  line `requiring him personally, or by his Agent, to shew his title. The notice issued in such cases shall state the`
  line `nature of the investigation which is intended, and shall call upon the alleged proprietor of the exempt lands`
  line `or interest held or claimed to be held exempt as aforesaid, to attend either personally or by an authorized`
  line `Agent, at a specified place, and within a specified period, (which shall never be less than two months from`
  line `the date of the notice being served,) to explain the nature of his tit le to hold such lands or interest exempt`
  line `as aforesaid, and to produce all the evidence forthcoming to prove it. The notice shall further explain that a`
  line `failure to comply with its terms will render the land, or interest to which it relates, liable to attach ment.`
  line `6. The notice shall be served upon the party holding or claiming to hold the land or interest exempt as`
  line `aforesaid, or, if his place of residence be not known, upon the person acting for him, or in default of such,`
  line `upon the person in charge of the lan d or interest.`
  line `7. If such persons cannot be found, a notice shall be posted in the Office of the Native Revenue Officer`
  line `of the District, and in the Chouree, or most public place of the village, where the land or interest under`
  line `inquiry is situated, calling on any person who may claim as proprietor to appear, either personally or by his`
  line `Agent, to prove his title within six months from the date of the notice, under penalty of the attachment of`
  line `the land or interest, and on failure of the appearance of a claiman t, the land or interest shall be liable to`
  line attachment.
  line `8. The attachment provided for by Rules 5 and 7 shall be enforced by the Collector or Chief Revenue`
  line `Authority of the District in which the land to which it relates is situated, at the written requisiti on of the`
  line `Inam Commissioner or his Assistant, which shall be a sufficient warrant to the Collector for the attachment`
  line `of the land, and for the collection of the rents accruing therefrom on account of Government during its`
  line attachment.
  line `9. As soon as possible after the receipt of the statements in each District, and of the evidence by which`
  line `they are supported, they shall be tested by the entries in the Government accounts and State records, and`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
