obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `which the forthcoming evidence does relate, it shall be continued permanently as official emolument, unless`
  line `the claimant's own statement renders this course improper.`
  line `Provision 5 th. — The provisions of this Rule are not in any way to apply to emoluments continued for`
  line `service performed to the State, as the Service Wuttuns of Desaees, S urdesaees, Nargowdas, Deshpandes,`
  line `Patells, Coolkurnees, Mhars, Tulwars, whose claims are to be disposed of according to the Rules which are`
  line `or may be established for the regulation of such holdings.`
  line `Provision 6 th. — It is to be understood that mere length of enjoyment of land as Inam by an official`
  line `person is not of itself sufficient to entitle a claim to be brought under this Rule.`
  line `Provision 7 th. — If a holding, claimed under this Rule, be found incapable of permanent continuance`
  line `under it, the claimant shall be allowed the advantages of any of the preceding Rules of this Schedule which`
  line `may be applicable to his case.`
  line `9. Regarding Provision for the Widows of the last incumbents of resumed holdings. — On the`
  line `resumption of any lands under the Rules of this Schedule a moiety, or other portion may be continued to`
  line `the Widows of the last incumbents during their lives, in cases of proved poverty and destitution.`
  line `Provision 1 st. — In the case of a holding, which is recognizable as an hereditary personal Inam, the`
  line `widow of a pro prietor who dies without surviving male issue, or other heirs to whom his Inam will of`
  line `necessity descend, is by right his sole heir, and during her life, the Inam cannot be regarded as having lapsed`
  line `to Government: it should therefore, in such a case, he co ntinued undiminished during the widow's life.`
  line `10. Regarding the exception of certain tenures from the application of these Rules. — These Rules`
  line `shall not be necessarily applicable to Jageers, Serinjams, or other tenures for service to Government, or`
  line `tenures of a Political nature, the titles and continuance of which shall be determined as heretofore under`
  line `such Rules as Government may find it necessary to issue from time to time.`
  line `11. Regarding the modification and interpretation of these Rules. — Any of these Rul es may be`
  line `relaxed in favor of claimants under instructions from the Governor of Bombay in Council, in whom shall`
  line `also be vested the power of interpreting the precise meaning of any of the Rules respecting which a question`
  line `may arise.`
